### Snippet 3: Performance Issue

Problems :
1- Uses ListView with children. it's matter because Every row is built eagerly, which is costly for long lists.
2- `Image.network` has no fallback. so if failed it's bad ui, also we should using CachedNetworkImage for better rendering with specify `cacheWidth`/`cacheHeight` to optimize the performance
3- constructor is not const.
4- we can make transaction item widget in separated file it's better for readability and will be reusable and easy to test.


Suggested fix :
```dart
class TransactionList extends StatelessWidget {
  const TransactionList({required this.transactions, super.key});

  final List<WalletTransactionEntity> transactions;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final locale = Localizations.localeOf(context).toLanguageTag();
    final dateFormat = DateFormat.yMMMd(locale).add_jm();

    return ListView.separated(
      itemCount: transactions.length,
      separatorBuilder: (_, _) => const SizedBox(height: 10),
      itemBuilder: (context, index) {
        final transaction = transactions[index];
        return TransactionListItem(
          transaction: transaction,
          date: dateFormat.format(transaction.createdAt),
        );
      },
    );
  }
}

class MerchantLogo extends StatelessWidget {
  const MerchantLogo({required this.logoUrl, required this.fallback, super.key});

  final String? logoUrl;
  final String fallback;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    if (logoUrl == null || logoUrl!.isEmpty) {
      return Text(fallback);
    }

    return Image.network(
      logoUrl!,
      width: 40,
      height: 40,
      cacheWidth: 80,
      cacheHeight: 80,
      fit: BoxFit.cover,
      errorBuilder: (_, _, _) => Text(fallback),
    );
  }
}
